		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But then EGA (16 colors out of 2bpc RGB) is not too far from the Master System.</div>
<br />
<br />This works only in 640x350. Due to IBM wanting compatibility of EGA in 200 lines modes with CGA monitors, only the 16 CGA text mode palette colors can be displayed in 200 line modes (640x200, 320x200 etc.). That is why most EGA graphics looks pretty bad.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
